summary: Hey!  You’re so amazing for all the positivity you’ve been putting out, thank you so much!  I was wondering, do you think that...
question: Hey!  You’re so amazing for all the positivity you’ve been putting out, thank you so much!  I was wondering, do you think that in another timeline where all the negativity of 2012 hadn’t occurred, would dan and phil be more public about their relationship?  I see the past couple of years after that as healing, but lately they seem to be testing the waters now more than ever. They’re both private people, but do you think that without those dark times they’d have eventually confirmed things?
answer:
hey b! oh my gosh y’all are too sweet <3 thank you for making this possible???

as for a different timeline - i know i’ve said it before in slightly different context but i think everything happens the way it’s meant to happen, and i want to be clear that, while i would never wish 2012 had happened, i take solace in the fact that dan wouldn’t change anything

but! for the sake of speculation, let’s entertain it. first and foremost, i’m working under the assumption that nothing about 2009/2010 was necessarily different, and i think we have a lot of internalized homophobia from that era regardless of 2012 happening. society as a whole was far more homophobic than it is now, and i think that did and would’ve still affected dnp. 

now, i wasn’t there at the time, so correct me if i’m wrong, but shipping wasn’t exactly nonexistent. so i’d say it was still very possible that it would’ve affected their comfort with being honest about their relationship negatively. 

but that’s then, let’s fast forward - i think society as a whole progressing toward a more accepting (and encouraging) mindset would’ve helped them regardless of their past (in the same way it’s helped them even factoring in 2012), but 2012 was very clearly a setback in a big way

aka this is my super long roundabout way of saying i think we’d have 2020!dnp in 2018 if 2012 hadn’t happened, but i won’t (and frankly can’t) begin to speculate what that would look like aside from the fact that i’m still fairly certain dnp wouldn’t be ‘official’

that last piece of my thoughts is tough bc it’s undeniably biased by the way dnp act now - i have a very hard time going back to 2012 and following a completely separate timeline down six years to determine what dnp would look like today. i mean, just think about how much they’ve changed in this timeline? 

anyway back to my point, tl;dr for everyone: chaos theory says there’s no way to confidently speculate on what dnp would look like now if 2012 didn’t happen, but my playing-it-safe guess would be that they’d be similar to how we might expect our dnp to act in a couple years. but at the end of the day, i think 2012 had to happen to get the incredible dnp we have today, and as dan said, he ‘wouldn’t change it for the world’

what do y’all think?
